“Well, hearsay is the poetry of truth. You are still a boy—quite a pretty boy to boot—so there are many things you won’t understand right now. I shall offer you only this observation: all people are basically naughty, but when it is done under the rose, when, for instance, you hasten to gorge yourself on jam in a dark corner, or send your imagination on God knows what errands, all that doesn’t count; nobody considers it a crime. Yet when a person frankly and assiduously satisfies